
Ruby-script to fetch MatchFact-player-stats from ATPWorldTour.com for two player, change it to per-game-stats (instead of absolute) if requested, and print it.

Usage: 
  ruby ATPStats.rb "<Player 1>" "<Player 2>" <Year> <Surface> <per-game-stats>
where year 0 = career, surface can be clay, grass or hard, 
and per-game-stats are true (on, default) or false (off).

Example:
  ruby ATPStats.rb "Roger Federer" "Novak Djokovic" 2012 grass

See bottom of ATPStats.rb for more details.